Example 1: Get employees and their managers
SELECT e1.name AS Employee, e2.name AS Manager
FROM employees e1
INNER JOIN employees e2 ON e1.manager_id = e2.id;
Example 2: Find students who share the same project
SELECT s1.name AS Student1, s2.name AS Student2, s1.project_id
FROM students s1
INNER JOIN students s2 ON s1.project_id = s2.project_id
AND s1.id <> s2.id;
Example 3: List products with similar categories
SELECT p1.product_name, p2.product_name, p1.category_id
FROM products p1
INNER JOIN products p2 ON p1.category_id = p2.category_id
AND p1.id <> p2.id;
6. NATURAL JOIN
Joins tables automatically using columns with the same name and datatype.
Example 1: Fetch students and their enrolled courses
SELECT * FROM students
NATURAL JOIN courses;
Example 2: Get all employees and their respective departments
SELECT * FROM employees
NATURAL JOIN departments;
Example 3: Retrieve customer orders without specifying join condition
SELECT * FROM customers
NATURAL JOIN orders;
